In one Bosnian town, a mosque was destroyed during the war in 1992, and a
church was later built on the spot where the mosque used to be; soon, however,
the church will be moved “a couple of hundred meters away so that the mosque
can be ‘rebuilt’ on its original location.” [More on
this](http://www.kakanien.ac.at/weblogs/balkancities/2009/06/moving+buildings+in+bosnia/)
– at _BalkanCities_.

